### Do
- Use [font] with `"[feature]"` on every text element — [why]
- Use weight [N] for [purpose] — [why]
- Apply [shadow color] for all elevated elements — [why]
- Use `#hex` for headings instead of `#000` — [why]
- Keep border-radius between [N]-[N]px — [why]
- [Each rule with WHY — intent, not just instruction]

### Don't
- Don't use weight [N] for [context] — [what to use instead]
- Don't use [color] for [purpose] — [why and alternative]
- Don't skip `"[feature]"` on text — [consequence]
- Don't use [radius]px on [element type] — [brand reasoning]
- [Each anti-pattern with consequence and alternative]

## 8. Responsive Behavior

### Breakpoints
| Name | Width | Key Changes |
|------|-------|-------------|
| Mobile | <[N]px | Single column, reduced heading sizes |
| Tablet | [N]-[N]px | 2-column grids, moderate padding |
| Desktop | [N]-[N]px | Full layout, 3-column feature grids |
| Large Desktop | >[N]px | Centered content with generous margins |

### Touch Targets
- Buttons: [N]px minimum height, [N]px padding
- Navigation links: adequate spacing for touch
- Mobile nav toggle with [N]px radius

### Collapsing Strategy
- Hero: [N]px display -> [N]px on mobile, weight maintained
- Navigation: horizontal -> hamburger toggle
- Cards: 3-col -> 2-col -> 1-col stacked
- Section spacing: [N]px+ -> [N]px on mobile
- Typography scale: [N]px -> [N]px -> [N]px across breakpoints

